===Origins===
[[File:Dora Milaje (Earth-616) from Black Panther Vol 4 14 0001.png|thumb|left|215px|[[T'Chaka (Earth-616)|T'Chaka]]'s Dora Milaje]]
The Dora Milaje (pronounced "DOR-ah muh-LAH-jay"){{r|Black Panther Vol 3 2}} are the personal bodyguards of the [[Black Panther]], recruited from every tribe of [[Wakanda]]. In addition with their protective function, they are also a pool of superior Wakandan women. An ancient tribal tradition, the Dora Milaje were assembled as potential queens for an unmarried king, maintaining the peace in Wakanda by ensuring that every tribe has the opportunity to put forward one of their daughters for the crown. Dora Milaje traditionally speak only in the Hausa dialect, and only to the king or each other. The practice of employing Dora Milaje was discontinued until recent years.{{r|Black Panther Vol 3 1}}{{r|Black Panther Annual Vol 2 #1}}

===Nakia and Okoye===
[[T'Challa (Earth-616)|T'Challa]], the latest Black Panther, reinstated the Dora Milaje program to calm tribal unrest in the kingdom after his proposed marriage to outsider, [[Monica Lynne (Earth-616)|Monica Lynne]], did not occur. The daughters of Wakanda, [[Nakia Shauku (Earth-616)|Nakia]] and [[Okoye (Earth-616)|Okoye]], became the first Dora Milaje to serve under T'Challa.{{r|Black Panther Vol 3 1}} Despite tradition and the girls' considerable skill and beauty, T'Challa viewed the teenage bodyguards like daughters, not actual wives-in-training.{{r|Black Panther Vol 3 8}}

Okoye understood her king's wishes, but Nakia dreamed of winning the king's love. When T'Challa was manipulated into passionately kissing Nakia while under the influence of [[Mephisto (Earth-616)|Mephisto]]'s illusions, it only fueled the girl's obsession.{{r|Black Panther Vol 3 3}} After Monica Lynne re-entered T'Challa's life, Nakia's jealousy caused her to eject Lynne from a fighter plane during a war, and she was expelled from the order of the Dora Milaje.{{r|{{cl|Black Panther Vol 3 11}}-[[Black Panther Vol 3 12|12]]}} In the months to come, Nakia was revived by [[Erik Killmonger (Earth-616)|Erik Killmonger]] and became an obsessive stalker of T'Challa, as well as his allies, under the alias of Malice.{{r|Black Panther Vol 3 24}}

===Queen Divine Justice===
Okoye was later joined by a new recruit in the Dora Milaje: [[Ce'Athauna Asira Davin (Earth-616)|Chanté Giovanni Brown]], of [[Chicago (Illinois)|Chicago]]. Princess of the outlawed [[Jabari Tribe (Earth-616)|Jabari Tribe]], [[White Gorilla Cult (Earth-616)|worshipers of the White Gorilla]], Chante had been exiled to the [[United States of America]] during the tribal warfare that killed her parents. She only learned of her Wakandan heritage when T'Challa approached her and inducted her into the Dora Milaje; however, it was still several months before T'Challa explained the circumstances of her parents' death.{{r|Black Panther Vol 3 35}}

===[[Civil War]]===
Over time, the order of the Dora Milaje expanded considerably, with more than a dozen active participants from the various tribes. Their service continued even after T'Challa's marriage to [[Ororo Munroe (Earth-616)|Ororo]].{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 18}}

[[File:S'Yan and Dora Milaje (Earth-616) from Black Panther Vol 4 6 0001.png|thumb|215px|left|[[S'Yan (Earth-616)|S'Yan]] and the Dora]]
During the [[Civil War (Event)|Civil War]], the Dora Milaje assisted T'Challa on a few occasions, on their quality of body-guards.When Storm and T'Challa visited the [[White House]], an incident led the Dora Milaje to battle [[James Rhodes (Earth-616)|War Machine]] and his [[Sentinel Squad O*N*E (Earth-616)|Sentinels]], and they were subsequently researched by the [[United States Government (Earth-616)|U.S. Government]].{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 23}}

Later, T'Challa intended to meet [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]], in order to organize the [[Secret Avengers (Civil War) (Earth-616)|resistance]] against the [[Superhuman Registration Act]], but was followed by the [[Natalia Romanova (Earth-616)|Black Widow]]. To get rid of her, T'Challa let two Dora Milaje confront her.{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 24}}

[[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]] and [[Cape-Killers (Earth-616)|Cape-Killers]] came to the [[Wakandan Embassy (New York City)|Wakandan Embassy]] in order to arrest the Dora Milaje who had attacked Rhodes, but were denied access to the embassy by Storm.{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 25}}

[[File:Dora Milaje (Earth-616) from Black Panther Vol 4 17 0001.png|165px|thumb|right|Urban-suited Dora Milaje]]
===[[Dark Reign]]===
After a fight with [[Victor von Doom (Earth-616)|Doom]], who cost the lives of two Dora Milaje and handicapped him for a time, T'Challa decided to initiate a specialized fighting style for the Adored Ones so they can better perform against robots and magic, which are Doom's primary weapons in battle. T'Challa set up a final test, which was a real fight, during which two Dora Milaje died among the thirty candidates.{{r|{{cl|Black Panther Vol 5 1}}-[[Black Panther Vol 5 12|12]]}}

===[[Doomwar Vol 1|Doomwar]]===
When Doom tried to take over Wakanda, the Dora Milaje paid a large tribute, with 500 Doras against the 80,000 soldiers of the [[Wakandan Army (Earth-616)|Wakandan Army]] and [[Wakandan Navy (Earth-616)|Navy]]. They then were used as [[Shuri (Earth-616)|Shuri]]'s army to destroy Doom's global network. T'Challa intended to kill Doom, sending [[Wade Wilson (Earth-616)|Deadpool]] and a commando of Dora Milaje known as the [[Midnight Angels (Earth-616)|Midnight Angels]].{{r|Doomwar #1|6}}

===[[Infinity (Event)|Infinity]]===
During the last moments of the [[Infinity (Event)|War]] with [[Thanos (Earth-616)|Thanos]], the Dora Milaje rejected T'Challa, denouncing to Shuri the [[Illuminati (Earth-616)|meetings]] of her brother with [[Namor McKenzie (Earth-616)|Namor]] while war was declared on [[Atlantis (Modern)|Atlantis]] following [[Avengers vs. X-Men|Namor's attack against Wakanda]] while he was under the [[Phoenix Five (Earth-616)|influence]] of the [[Phoenix Force (Earth-616)|Phoenix]]. They broke their spears symbolically and fully came under the orders of the Queen Shuri.{{r|New Avengers Vol 3 12}}

